	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=56573><span id= >Valdon</span></a><br><span id=notbold>520 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.85]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Bards seem to fit into no other class. Them and enchanters seem to be VERY unique. I have so many questions. I have a lvl 12 bard. I never realized the potential untill I started reading more. We get snare,root,DD,AoE,sow,clarity (of sorts) ETC. They are a powerhouse of self combo/stacking songs. My questions right now.<br><br>1. Some songs apperently DO take mana now. Denon's Desperate Dirge&nbsp;&nbsp;and Solon's Bewitching Bravura... So will a CLARITY be usefull to a bard? Because a CLARITY with the MANA REGEN.... would be... sick.<br><br>2. You can have a PROCK/SPELL and an EFFECT on you. If bard songs stack with most spells, what is it clasified as? an Effect?<br><br>3. I am looking for an EASY way to twist songs. If ANYONE has an advanced MACRO command line please post it. stuff like<br>/cast 1, /pause 10 - ETC.<br>I know there are some macro programs like &quot;xybot&quot; but i play at a lan party place right now until I can make my pc.<br><br>Stuff like the Additional dammage, plus the DD spell and attacking... is just sick. Especially if you could charm somehting to help you too.<br><br>Just talk to me people. Im pretty interested int he Bard class.</p>&nbsp;<br>· 'Valdon Gravedancer' Terris-Thule. Dwarven Cleric 32nd season.<br>· 'Junglebug Sugarpants' Terris-Thule. Halfling Druid. 39th season.<br>· 'Shinook Eldergod' Terris-Thule. Troll Shaman of 32nd season</td></td></tr>
